20His%20constant%20lying%20offends%3B%20his%20cruelty%20offends%3B%20his%20racism%20offends%3B%20his%20misogyny%20offends%3B%20his%20open%20contempt%20for%20%E2%80%9Closers%E2%80%9D%20offends%3B%20his%20lack%20of%20remorse%20offends%3B%20his%20vanity%20offends%3B%20his%20affinity%20for%20chaos%20offends%3B%20his%20admiration%20for%20dictators%20offends%3B%20his%20vow%20for%20retribution%20and%20revenge%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cenemies%20of%20the%20people%E2%80%9D%20(anyone%20who%20has%20crossed%20him%20or%20might%20cross%20him)%20offends%3B%20his%20promise%20to%20begin%20%E2%80%9Cmass%20deportation%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9C25%20million%E2%80%9D%20illegal%20immigrants%20on%20Day%201%20offends%3B%20his%20vow%20to%20upend%20world%20trade%20by%20imposing%20a%2020%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20goods%20and%2060%25%20on%20Chinese%20goods%20offends%3B%20his%20promise%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20women%20whether%20they%20like%20it%20or%20not%E2%80%9D%20offends%3B%20his%20commitment%20to%20dismiss%20climate%20change%20and%20pursue%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdrill%2C%20baby%2C%20drill%E2%80%9D%20energy%20policy%20offends%3B%20his%20commitment%20to%20end%20Obamacare%20offends.%20The%20list%20is%20endless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20Trump's%20World...%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Trump%20is%20the%20first%20Republican%20in%2020%20years%20to%20win%20the%20popular%20vote%2C%20and%20the%20MAGA%20movement%20has%20given%20him%20unfettered%20power%20by%20securing%20both%20the%20Senate%20and%20the%20House.%20The%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20already%20aligned%20with%20him%206-3%20and%20has%20effectively%20granted%20him%20virtual%20immunity%20from%20any%20presidential%20acts.%20Project%202025%20has%20a%20blueprint%20ready%20to%20fulfil%20his%20promise%20to%20crush%20the%20%E2%80%9CDeep%20State%E2%80%9D%20(i.e.%2C%20federal%20officials%20committed%20to%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law)%20and%20replace%20up%20to%2050%2C000%20federal%20employees%20with%20loyalists.%20The%20independence%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20and%20the%20Justice%20Department%20will%20be%20under%20threat.%20All%20of%20this%20has%20been%20clear%20as%20daylight%20since%20Trump%20announced%20his%20re-run%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20won%20because%20he%20successfully%20positioned%20himself%20as%20the%20Agent%20of%20Change%20(%E2%80%98Trump%20will%20Fix%20It')%2C%20addressing%20the%20issues%20that%20affect%20his%20core%20voter%20base%E2%80%9462%25%20of%20Americans%20without%20a%20college%20degree.%20These%20voters%2C%20who%20typically%20show%20little%20interest%20in%20politics%20but%20are%20deeply%20focused%20on%20improving%20their%20material%20well-being%20and%20preserving%20their%20cultural%20values%2C%20were%20key%20to%20his%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20what%20affects%20them%3F%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20important%20issues%20include%20rising%20costs%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%3A%20grocery%20prices%20up%2020%25%2C%20rents%20up%2040%25.%20There%20are%20also%20concerns%20about%20men's%20self-image%3A%20girls%20outperforming%20boys%20in%20school%20and%20college%2C%20the%20%23MeToo%20movement%2C%20and%20college-educated%20women%20seeing%20the%20highest%20increases%20in%20income%20and%20status.%20Then%20there%20is%20what%20many%20perceive%20as%20the%20imposition%20of%20%E2%80%98Wokeism'%3A%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20accepting%20the%20full%20rights%20and%20recognition%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%20community%2C%20but%20also%20about%20children%20having%20the%20right%20to%20change%20their%20gender%20before%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fear%20Of%20Immigrants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20there%20are%20deeply%20held%20beliefs%20based%20on%20fear%20and%20misinformation.%20I%20know%20a%20Texas-based%20psychotherapist%20whose%20patient%20confided%20that%20she%20was%20afraid%20to%20go%20out%20at%20night%20due%20to%20fear%20of%20immigrants%2C%20even%20though%20she%20employs%20a%20migrant%E2%80%94likely%20an%20undocumented%20worker%E2%80%94as%20a%20housekeeper.%20Another%20patient%20believes%20Trump%20was%20sent%20by%20God%20and%20that%20the%20opposition%20party%20was%20sent%20by%20the%20Devil.%20Neither%20patient%20suffers%20from%20psychosis%3B%20these%20are%20culturally%20sanctioned%20beliefs%2C%20according%20to%20the%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there%20are%20outright%20misconceptions%E2%80%94such%20as%20the%20belief%20that%20tariffs%20won't%20raise%20the%20cost%20of%20household%20goods%2C%20or%20that%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20with%20no%20new%20wars%2C%20proves%20he%20could%20end%20the%20Ukraine%20and%20Middle%20East%20conflicts%20immediately%20upon%20taking%20office.%20There%20is%20also%20the%20notion%20that%20the%20mass%20deportation%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20would%20not%20cripple%20industries%20that%20rely%20heavily%20on%20immigrant%20labour%2C%20like%20the%20US%20meat%20industry.%20According%20to%20The%20Economist%2C%20roughly%20half%20of%20the%20labour%20on%20US%20farms%20is%20undocumented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20same%20Texas-based%20psychotherapist%20couldn't%20believe%20his%20eyes%20when%20he%20saw%20a%20massive%20billboard%20in%20rural%20Texas%20proclaiming%2C%20%E2%80%9CBorn%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Thinks%20Like%20a%20Texan.%E2%80%9D%20That's%20the%20story%20Trump%20sold%20to%20voters.%20And%20in%20politics%E2%80%94especially%20electoral%20politics%E2%80%94perception%20is%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20There%20Really%20A%20Tectonic%20Shift%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20what%20some%20view%20as%20an%20impending%20apocalypse%20for%20the%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20Trump's%20win%20in%20the%20popular%20vote%20was%20narrow%3A%2075.8%20million%20votes%20(50.2%25)%20to%20Kamala%20Harris's%2072.8%20million%20votes%20(48.2%25)%2C%20with%20nearly%20all%20votes%20counted.%20In%202016%2C%20Biden%20led%20Trump%20by%207%20million%20votes.%20But%20credit%20where%20it's%20due%E2%80%94Trump%20won%20the%20popular%20vote%20by%20actively%20pursuing%20it%2C%20rallying%20supporters%20in%20New%20York%20and%20California%2C%20even%20though%20those%20blue%20states'%20electoral%20college%20votes%20were%20never%20in%20play%20for%20him.%20This%20effort%20came%20in%20the%20final%20weeks%20of%20the%20campaign%20when%20conventional%20wisdom%20would%20suggest%20focusing%20on%20the%20seven%20key%20swing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20true%20is%20the%20talk%20of%20a%20tectonic%20shift%20in%20the%20vote%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20Republican%20social%20coalition%3F%20It%20is%20true%20that%20the%20identity%20that%20moved%20the%20non-White%20vote%20to%20Trump%20was%20their%20working-class%2C%20non-college-educated%20identity.%20These%20voters%20believed%20that%20Trump%20would%20do%20a%20better%20job%20of%20bringing%20back%20jobs%20lost%20to%20Mexico%2C%20addressing%20their%20affordability%20crisis%2C%20preserving%20their%20conservative%20cultural%20values%2C%20and%20securing%20their%20legal%20immigrant%20status%20by%20deporting%20illegal%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20should%20have%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20Pre-election%20polls%20from%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fem%3Efound%20a%20surprising%20affinity%20between%20Trump's%20views%20and%20those%20of%20Latinos%20and%20Black%20voters.%20Four%20out%20of%20ten%20Hispanic%20voters%20and%20one%20out%20of%20five%20Black%20voters%20had%20a%20favourable%20impression%20of%20Trump.%20A%20majority%20of%20them%20sympathized%20with%20his%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%E2%80%9D%20foreign%20policy.%20Only%2020%25%20of%20Hispanic%20voters%20and%2026%25%20of%20Black%20voters%20felt%20that%20the%20economic%20conditions%20were%20good%20or%20excellent.%20Median%20weekly%20wages%20for%20full-time%20Black%20workers%20had%20risen%20steeply%20during%20Trump's%20presidency%20but%20essentially%20stagnated%20under%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20absolute%20numbers%2C%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20non-White%20vote%20has%20not%20been%20as%20significant%20as%20it%20is%20often%20portrayed%2C%20as%20columnist%20Thomas%20Edsall%20points%20out%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CRoughly%20six%20in%20ten%20Hispanics%20voted%20for%20Joe%20Biden%3B%20five%20in%20ten%20for%20Kamala%20Harris.%20Nine%20out%20of%20ten%20Black%20voters%20chose%20Biden%3B%20eight%20in%20ten%20for%20Harris.%20More%20than%20four-fifths%20of%20Trump's%20votes%20came%20from%20White%20voters.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20won%20because%20he%20has%20excellent%20political%20instincts%20and%20because%20people%20know%20exactly%20what%20he%20stands%20for.%20His%20views%20on%20trade%20and%20immigration%20were%20shaped%20years%20before%20he%20entered%20politics.%20%E2%80%9CI%20believe%20very%20strongly%20in%20tariffs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20a%20journalist%20in%201989.%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20is%20being%20ripped%20off.%E2%80%9D%20In%20his%202000%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20America%20We%20Deserve%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Cour%20current%20laxness%20toward%20illegal%20immigration%20shows%20a%20recklessness%20and%20disregard%20for%20those%20who%20live%20here%20legally.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERich-Poor%20Divide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20particularly%20disturbing%20for%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20is%20that%20this%20election%20has%20reinforced%20the%20post-2012%20electoral%20reality%3A%20the%20less%20well-off%20are%20siding%20with%20Trump%2C%20while%20the%20college-educated%2C%20coastal%20elites%20are%20aligned%20with%20the%20Democrats.%20With%20White%20Americans%20comprising%2067%25%20of%20the%20population%20and%2062%25%20of%20Americans%20lacking%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20the%20Democrats%20will%20need%20to%20look%20beyond%20conventional%20politicians%E2%80%94those%20who%20twist%20and%20turn%20their%20positions%20to%20conform%2C%20always%20erring%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%E2%80%94to%20lead%20the%20fightback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20as%20we%20all%20know%2C%20Trump%20can%20be%20his%20own%20worst%20enemy.%20He%20is%20entirely%20transactional.%20For%20him%2C%20loyalty%20is%20always%20one-way.%20His%20insecurity%20prevents%20him%20from%20sharing%20the%20limelight%20with%20anyone%20else.%20His%20vanity%20leaves%20him%20vulnerable%20to%20manipulation.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20he%20is%20not%20the%20best%20judge%20of%20character%2C%20and%20his%20loyalists%20continue%20to%20cycle%20through%20a%20revolving%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeam%20Trump%2C%202.0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quote%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20column%20is%20from%20Kellyanne%20Conway%2C%20the%20Republican%20pollster%20who%20worked%20with%20Trump%20from%202013%20and%20managed%20his%202016%20campaign.%20She%20later%20joined%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration%20but%20left%20amid%20a%20public%20feud%20with%20her%20teenage%20daughter%20in%20August%202020%2C%20who%20lambasted%20her%20personally%20and%20politically%20and%20even%20threatened%20legal%20separation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConway%20is%20not%20the%20only%20person%20who%20was%20once%20with%20Trump%20but%20is%20no%20longer.%20Steve%20Bannon%2C%20Trump's%20chief%20ideologue%20and%20speechwriter%2C%20is%20not%20in%20the%20fold%20anymore.%20In%20his%20place%20is%20Stephen%20Miller%2C%20the%20architect%20of%20Trump's%20hardline%20immigration%20policies.%20Trump's%20daughter%20Ivanka%20and%20son-in-law%20Jared%20Kushner%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20Don%20Jr.%2C%20who%20is%20now%20in%20charge%20of%20conducting%20the%20%E2%80%9Cloyalty%20test%E2%80%9D%20for%20anyone%20seeking%20to%20join%20the%20administration.%20John%20Kelly%2C%20Trump's%20longest-serving%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20who%20called%20him%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfascist%2C%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20Susie%20Wiles%2C%20Trump's%20campaign%20manager.%20Wiles%20is%20known%20for%20her%20discipline%20and%20focus%20on%20facilitating%20whatever%20catches%20Trump's%20fancy.%20The%20big%20question%20is%3A%20how%20long%20will%20she%20last%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94which%20Trump%20both%20loathes%20and%20loves%20to%20read%E2%80%94has%20come%20in%20for%20criticism%20for%20suggesting%20that%20Trump%20will%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Clame%20duck%E2%80%9D%20president%2C%20given%20that%20the%2022nd%20Amendment%20to%20the%20US%20Constitution%20prohibits%20a%20third%20presidential%20term.%20Critics%20accused%20the%20paper%20of%20sour%20grapes.%20However%2C%20in%20an%20unintended%20way%2C%20the%20paper%20has%20highlighted%20Trump's%20main%20dilemma%3A%20what%20legacy%20does%20he%20want%20to%20leave%20behind%3F%20He%20has%20mined%20the%20deep%20divide%20and%20distrust%20of%20Washington%20in%20US%20society%20to%20become%20the%20most%20dominant%20figure%20in%20American%20politics%20for%20the%20past%20decade.%20Does%20he%20now%20pivot%20to%20statesmanship%20and%20attempt%20to%20unite%20the%20country%3F%20Or%20does%20he%20pander%20to%20his%20MAGA%20base%20and%20give%20full%20rein%20to%20his%20thirst%20for%20revenge%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERein%20Of%20Uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20signs%20are%20ominous.%20Trump's%20nomination%20of%20the%20highly%20controversial%20Congressman%20Matt%20Gaetz%2C%20who%20is%20under%20investigation%20for%20ethics%20violations%2C%20as%20Attorney%20General%20has%20even%20alarmed%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CHe's%20a%20nominee%20for%20those%20who%20want%20the%20law%20used%20for%20political%20revenge%2C%20and%20it%20won't%20end%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20case%20of%20%3Cem%3EFox%20News%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehost%20Pete%20Hegseth%2C%20who%20has%20been%20outspoken%20against%20the%20Pentagon's%20%E2%80%9Cwoke%E2%80%9D%20policies%20regarding%20racial%20and%20transgender%20equity%2C%20and%20the%20appointment%20of%20former%20Democratic%20presidential%20contender%20Tulsi%20Gabbard%2C%20now%20a%20Trump%20loyalist%2C%20as%20Director%20of%20National%20Intelligence%2C%20raise%20further%20concerns.%20Gabbard%20has%20shown%20no%20evidence%20of%20expertise%20in%20intelligence.%20No%20one%20should%20be%20surprised%20by%20this%20turn%20of%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Ajay%20Kumar%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist.%20He%20is%20the%20former%20Managing%20Editor%2C%20Business%20Standard%2C%20and%20former%20Executive%20Editor%2C%20Economic%20Times.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731669840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F8iek7258_donald-trump-afp_625x300_09_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnow-that-he-has-won-will-trump-try-to-unite-america-again-7026345%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you're%20looking%20for%20an%20insight%20that%20helps%20explain%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20election%20and%20why%20it%20happened%2C%20consider%20this%20observation%20from%20a%20key%20player%20in%20US%20politics%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20difference%20between%20what%20offends%20people%20and%20what%20affects%20them.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnow-that-he-has-won-will-trump-try-to-unite-america-again-7026345%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Star's%20'Weakness'%20Exposed%20During%20Practice%20At%20Perth%20-%20Report's%20Big%20Claim%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndian%20cricket%20team%20batter%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Sarfaraz%20Khan%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F64385-sarfaraz-naushad-khan-playerprofile%5C%22%3ESarfaraz%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%20struggled%20massively%20during%20t