5C%22%3EA380%20jets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ATSB%20investigation%20found%20that%20the%20tool%20had%20been%20inside%20one%20of%20the%20plane's%20four%20engines%20since%20a%20previous%20maintenance%20check%20on%20December%206%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20superjumbo%20jet%20had%20flown%2034%20cycles%2C%20or%20294%20hours%2C%20with%20the%20nylon%20tool%20in%20the%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20conclusion%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BForeign%20object%20debris%20and%20damage%20can%20pose%20a%20significant%20threat%20to%20the%20safe%20operation%20of%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20said%20that%20an%20engineer%20left%20the%20tool%20in%20the%20engine%20inlet%20because%20they%20believed%20it%20would%20be%20needed%20by%20somebody%20else%20later.%20Subsequent%20inspections%20after%20their%20task%20failed%20to%20spot%20the%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ATSB%20investigation%20found%20that%20maintenance%20engineers%20did%20not%20notice%20the%20tool%20had%20been%20left%20in%20the%20engine's%20low-pressure%20compressor%20case%20when%20conducting%20checks%20for%20foreign%20objects%20at%20the%20completion%20of%20the%20borescope%20inspection%20task%2C%26quot%3B%20ATSB%20Chief%20Commissioner%20Angus%20Mitchell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFurther%2C%20maintenance%20engineers%20did%20not%20commence%20the%20lost%20tool%20procedure%20once%20the%20tool%20had%20been%20identified%20as%20missing%2C%20and%20the%20certifying%20engineer%20released%20the%20aircraft%20for%20service%20with%20the%20tool%20unaccounted%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20tool%20was%20discovered%2C%20Qantas%20said%20it%20briefed%20engineering%20staff%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20returning%20all%20tools%20and%20issued%20an%20internal%20safety%20directive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20take%20this%20extremely%20seriously%20and%20while%20there%20was%20no%20damage%20sustained%20to%20the%20engine%2C%20it%20is%20criti