%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAryan%20Nangia%20created%20LaunchPad%20to%20teach%20students%20future-proof%20skills%20for%20free.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20needed%20content%20that%20was%20easy%20to%20understand%2C%20practical%2C%20and%20specifically%20designed%20to%20address%20the%20unique%20challenges%20we%20face%20when%20building%20something%20from%20scratch%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20This%20realisation%20became%20the%20catalyst%20for%20LaunchPad%2C%20a%20platform%20created%20to%20fill%20that%20gap%20%E2%80%94%20empowering%20young%20people%20to%20navigate%20the%20complexities%20of%20ideation%2C%20development%2C%20and%20execution%20with%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%2015-year-old%20Aryan%20took%20the%20leap%20and%20started%20LaunchPad%20as%20a%20club%20at%20his%20school.%20What%20began%20as%20a%20small%20group%20of%20students%20learning%20how%20to%20build%20real-world%20projects%20soon%20expanded%20into%20a%20global%20initiative.%20Now%2C%20less%20than%20two%20years%20later%2C%20LaunchPad%20has%20scaled%20beyond%20a%20school%20club%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F295026%2Fhealthcare-startup-to-manage-pcos-for-indian-women-by-sisters-raises-funding%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20serves%20students%20across%2015%20schools%20in%20five%20countries.%20Today%2C%20the%20team%20has%20expanded%20to%20a%20dynamic%20group%20of%2015%20to%2020%20young%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaunchPad%E2%80%99s%20mission%20is%20simple%3A%20to%20help%20students%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2012%20and%2017%20learn%20essential%20skills%20and%20gain%20hands-on%20experience%20in%20project%20development.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20about%20learning%20how%20to%20code%20or%20design.%20La