ivity%20and%20preventing%20compaction%20to%20managing%20pH%2C%20controlling%20erosion%2C%20and%20retaining%20moisture%2C%20these%20solutions%20address%20key%20challenges%20faced%20by%20Indian%20farmers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Hemlata%20Chouhan%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F374594%2Fwinter-soil-health-india-tips-farmers-temperature-crops-compaction-microbial-activity%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dengue%20%26amp%3B%20Jaundice%20Drove%20These%20Teen%20Sisters%20To%20Build%20a%20Successful%20Goat%20Milk%20Business%20in%20Punjab%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20small%20but%20lively%20town%20of%20Bahadurgarh%2C%20located%20just%2020%20km%20southwest%20of%20Patiala%20city%20in%20Punjab%2C%20two%20teenage%20sisters%2C%20Mannat%20and%20Eknoor%20Mehmi%2C%20have%20turned%20a%20family%20necessity%20into%20a%20thriving%20business.%20India%20Goat%20Milk%20Farm%2C%20which%20began%20just%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20was%20born%20out%20of%20a%20personal%20health%20crisis%20when%20Mannat%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20jaundice.%20A%20well-meaning%20elder%20suggested%20that%20goat%20milk%20could%20help%20in%20her%20recovery%2C%20leading%20their%20father%2C%20Harbhajan%20Singh%2C%20to%20invest%20Rs%2020%2C000%20in%20a%20single%20goat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20initial%20days%2C%20Mannat%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20quite%20young%20and%20had%20always%20wanted%20a%20pet%20dog%20or%20a%20cat%2C%20so%20we%20were%20just%20very%20excited%20about%20having%20a%20goat%20at%20least.%E2%80%9D%20Once%20the%20first%20goat%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20female%20kid%20and%20the%20newborn%20was%20fed%20its%20first%20milk%2C%20the%20family%20began%20incorporating%20it%20into%20their%20daily%20diet.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20we%20started%20using%20the%20milk%20in%20our%20house%20every%20day%2C%20we%20saw%20great%20results%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20didn%E2%80%99t%20g